race.comment: BEAUTIFUL JEWEL (6) is knocking on the door this campaign and looks well placed despite the wide alley. With Pannell aboard she has the slight edge and can finally break through. I CATCHEM FOX (4) arrives with solid Victorian form and a strong record at this track. The claim helps and he's expected to be right in the thick of things. FALAISE (1) could find himself in a tricky spot from the low draw but if the gaps appear, he has the turn of foot to give them a scare. Interesting runner on the quick back-up. BOWER BOY (8) improved sharply second-up when closing off into the frame. Open to further progression and with Holder sticking, he's in the mix. WILD WINNER (7) is a consistent mare who scored here three weeks ago. Third-up now and still improving, she must be taken seriously.
